<div id="review_3599981383" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3599981383" />
    <a title="Ramon van Dam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36069918-ramon-van-dam"><img alt="Ramon van Dam" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1413643045p2/36069918.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3599981383?book_show_action=true">Nov 14, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ramon van Dam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ramon van Dam" href="/user/show/36069918-ramon-van-dam">Ramon van Dam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780755312184" href="/book/show/198505.The_Demon_in_the_Freezer">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3599981383" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5657363650497041375">Just some light reading for 2020 😇<br/><br/>Man, this was again quite scary... While Preston&apos;s &quot;The Hot Zone&quot; had ebola at its center, this time around he focused on smallpox and anthrax. Two infectious deseases with high R0 values that spread rapidly as aerosoles, does that ring a bell?<br/><br/>I already really liked that previous non-fiction dark biology book by the same author, but this one is better in multiple regards. It&apos;s not as repetitive and doesn&apos;t focus too much on Preston himself, while we still learn </span>
  <span id="freeText5657363650497041375" style="display:none">Just some light reading for 2020 😇<br /><br />Man, this was again quite scary... While Preston's "The Hot Zone" had ebola at its center, this time around he focused on smallpox and anthrax. Two infectious deseases with high R0 values that spread rapidly as aerosoles, does that ring a bell?<br /><br />I already really liked that previous non-fiction dark biology book by the same author, but this one is better in multiple regards. It's not as repetitive and doesn't focus too much on Preston himself, while we still learn about the nature of these viruses and the science around them.<br /><br />This year we've all received a big wake-up call, but I think it wouldn't hurt if much more people would read this book. Even with the forced education that we all went through these past eight months the real threat still hasn't landed I'm afraid.<br /><br />Not uplifting, but oh so important in my opinion.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5657363650497041375" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

